    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/8–2054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_ALGERFMJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Alger</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d576fn1">Sent also to Paris for <persName
                            corresp="#p_BRUCEDKE1">Bruce</persName> and the Ambassador eyes only.
                        Repeated to London, Bonn, Rome, The Hague, and Luxembourg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-20T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 20, 1954—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154. From <persName corresp="#p_TOMLINSONWM1">Tomlinson</persName>. Limit
                    distribution strictly. According to <persName corresp="#p_DESTAERCKEA1">De
                        Staercke</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFRANCEP1">Mendes-France</persName> had sharp
                    exchange after this morning’s session. <persName corresp="#p_MENDESFRANCEP1"
                        >Mendes</persName> said conference would have to fail unless other countries
                    agreed their Parliaments should take some new action. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPAAKPH1">Spaak</persName> said that if France insisted on this,
                    five countries would issue common declaration. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MENDESFRANCEP1">Mendes</persName> angrily said it was
                    unthinkable that other western European nations emphasize divergence by
                    isolating France in such a manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ALGERFMJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Alger</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
